/*!
\page elementary_vec VEC Reshape to a Vector

<p>
Section: \ref sec_elementary "Elementary Functions"
\section Usage
Reshapes an n-dimensional array into a column vector.  The general
syntax for its use is
\verbatim
   y = vec(x)
\endverbatim
where <tt>x</tt> is an n-dimensional array (not necessarily numeric).  This
function is equivalent to the expression <tt>y = x(:)</tt>.
\section Example
A simple example of the <tt>vec</tt> operator reshaping a 2D matrix:

\if FRAGMENT
frag_elementary_vec_000.m
0
A = [1,2,4,3;2,3,4,5]
vec(A)
\endif


\verbinclude frag_elementary_vec_000.m.out 

